From Greg Neill Subject Wanted source for tuning capacitors Hello The other day I was feeling a tad nostalgic and thought about constructing an old time crytal radio I figured on substituting a modern germanium diode for the crystal and winding the antenna coil The only problem I seem to have is in locating a source for a tuning capacitor you know the old meshed plate variable condensers which used to be the mainstay for tuning Well these things seem to be all but extinct in their original catalog Trimmer capacitors are relatively abundant but are not really suitable for this So can anyone point me to a supplier of tuning capacitors in the pF range Greg Neill ounce ouns The standard unit of HNSX Supercomputers prevention equal to one pound of